00030   int dimension = positions.size();
00031

00328 void Parser_Eval::eval_fct(const DoubleTabs& variables, DoubleTab& val) const
00329 {
00330   int dim;
00331   int pos_size = val.dimension(0);
00332 
00333   assert(fonction_.size() == 1);
00334 
00335   int nb_dim = val.nb_dim();
00336   int nbvars = variables.size();
00337 
00338   Parser_U& fct = parser(0);
00339 
00340   if (nb_dim==1)
00341     {
00342       for (int i=0; i<pos_size; i++)
00343         {
00344           for (int ivar=0; ivar<nbvars; ivar++)
00345             fct.setVar(ivar,variables[ivar](i));
00346 
00347           val(i) = fct.eval();
00348         }
00349     }
00350   else
00351     {
00352       dim = val.dimension(1);
00353       for (int i=0; i<pos_size; i++)
00354         {
00355           for(int k=0; k<dim; k++)
00356             {
00357               for (int ivar=0; ivar<nbvars; ivar++)
00358                 fct.setVar(ivar,variables[ivar](i,k));
00359               val(i,k) = fct.eval();
00360             }
00361         }
00362     }
00363 }
